-- 
Australia Loses at Cricket World Cup; England, India Make Quarterfinals

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-03-19T17:52:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-19/south-africa-wins-at-cricket-world-cup-england-india-make-quarterfinals.html
Pakistan ended  Australia ’s unbeaten
run at the Cricket World Cup, as India and England qualified for
the quarterfinals.  Pakistan won by four wickets in Colombo, Sri Lanka, to halt
the defending champion’s 34-match unbeaten run in the tournament.
Umar Gul was 3-30 as Australia was dismissed for 176, and Umar 
Akmal scored 44 not out to help Pakistan reach 178-6 in 41 overs 
for the win.  Pakistan wins Group A with 10 points, one more than Sri
Lanka and Australia and two ahead of New Zealand. The top four
teams in each of the seven-team groups advance to the
quarterfinals.    South Africa  beat Bangladesh by 206 runs to finish atop
Group B and also send  India  and England into the quarterfinals.
Robin Peterson took 4-12 as Bangladesh was bowled out for 78 in
response to South Africa’s 284-8 in Mirpur, Bangladesh.  South Africa finished with 10 points, while India and
England have seven. West Indies has six points, the same as
Bangladesh, heading to its final game tomorrow against India.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
